Reasoning: The paper discusses the relationship between communication systems and knowledge, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it deals with natural language processing and communication. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are also relevant as they deal with the social organization of knowledge and communication systems. cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are less likely but still relevant as they deal with the impact of technology on society and the complexity of communication systems.
